<h2 id="history">9. Historical Bear Markets: What the Data Shows</h2>

<p>Let's look at what actually happened in previous crypto bear markets, and what it means for 2026:</p>

<h3>The 2018 Bear Market (The "Crypto Winter")</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Bitcoin fell from ~$19,700 to ~$3,200 (-84%)</li>
    <li>The bottom was reached in December 2018</li>
    <li>Recovery to new ATH took ~3 years (December 2020)</li>
    <li>Those who DCA'd through 2018-2019 saw 10-20x returns by 2021</li>
</ul>

<h3>The 2022 Bear Market (The "Triple Crash")</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Bitcoin fell from ~$69,000 to ~$15,500 (-77%)</li>
    <li>Solana fell from ~$260 to ~$8 (-96%) ” one of the most brutal drawdowns</li>
    <li>The bottom was reached in November 2022 (FTX collapse capitulation)</li>
    <li>Recovery to new ATH took ~2 years (SOL hit $260+ by late 2024)</li>
    <li>Those who bought SOL at $8 saw a 30x return</li>
</ul>

